451â†’/**
452â†’ * A helper to delay execution of a task that is being requested often, while
453â†’ * preventing accumulation of consecutive executions, while the task runs.
454â†’ *
455â†’ * The mail man is clever and waits for a certain amount of time, before going
456â†’ * out to deliver letters. While the mail man is going out, more letters arrive
457â†’ * and can only be delivered once he is back. Once he is back the mail man will
458â†’ * do one more trip to deliver the letters that have accumulated while he was out.
